I would like to build a good size community of developers that could devote some time to this project.  I am still in the progress of gathering requirements. If you are interested in being involved, please contact me.

value.Title: Analysis Services Parent-Child Dimension Naturalizer
value.Description:
Parent/Child dimensions, wherein each member references the ID of its parent member rather than being specified on a specific level of a hierarchy, are often a cause for poor performance in Analysis Services databases. One way of dealing with this is to convert a poorly performing P/C dimension table to a natural one. Instead of having a member ID key column and a corresponding parent ID column, which must be referenced recursively until the root of the hierarchy tree is reached, a converted table contains one column for each level of the hierarchy in addition to the member ID, and each ancestor ID of a member is specified in the level column associated with it in the table. This prevents the requirement of traversal of the hierarchy tree in order to identify each member's location in the hierarchy.

Here is a simple example:

                      # Member 4

1 	0 	xxxxxx
2 	1 	yyyyy
3 	2 	zzzzzz
4 	2 	xyxyxy

MemberID 	Level0ID 	Level1ID 	Level2ID 	MemberData

2 	1 	2 	null 	yyyyyy
3 	1 	2 	3 	zzzzzzz
4 	1 	2 	4 	xyxyxyxy
